[The chief veterinary officer of France, Dr Jean-Luc Angot, published on 4 Jan 2012 a detailed (8 pages) document "note de service DGAL/SDSPA/N2012-8007 du 04 janvier 2012," incorporating a call for alertness and specified instructions for surveillance and sample collection in case of suspected SBV-affected offspring, particularly in northeast France. Although SBV is not a notifiable disease in France, thus its reporting is not obligatory by law, farmers and veterinarians are encouraged to report any suspicion. The document, which also includes a case definition, is available (in French) at http://agriculture.gouv.fr/IMG/pdf/DGALN20128007Z.pdf. The only French laboratory designated for SBV diagnosis is the virology department at Maison Alfort.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of France can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/1He9. The departments of Moselle and Meurthe-et-Moselle are in the Lorraine region, northeast France, bordering Belgium and Germany. They can be seen on the map at http://www.trussel.com/maig/image/frdeptb.jpg.

Official confirmation (or otherwise) of the identification of SBV in France will be appreciated. In case affirmative, additional information will be helpful. - Mod.AS]
